                            <comment id="16814965" author="hossman" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2019 00:32:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attaching a quick and ditry test patch that shows how ZkClientClusterStateProvider doesn&apos;t complain if you try to use it after it&apos;s already been closed &#8211; but the test always leaks objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll work up another patch that hardens ZkClientClusterStateProvider to throw AlreadyClosedException in this type of sitaution, and update the test to assert that it&apos;s thrown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16815007" author="hossman" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2019 01:55:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;here&apos;s an updated patch that hardens ZkClientClusterStateProvider so that any attempt to use it after close will throw AlreadyClosedException.&#160; test updated to assert this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that this change also update ZkStateReader to implement SolrClosable so we can assert that a ZkClientClusterStateProvider constructed from an existing/reused ZkStateReader won&apos;t incorrectly close it.&#160; (this seemed like a good/minor enhancement to ZkStateReader independent of this issue)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16815132" author="ab" created="Thu, 11 Apr 2019 07:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch! the patch looks good to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
